Description: Fragment of a pottery krater (?) or amphora; half of triple-reeded handle and part of shoulder, cream slip on outside, top of handle painted red. Hard, coarse, porous, orange/brown clay, Munsell 2.5YR 5/6 (red); light and dark mica.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 322)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
